'"note": her DURABLE MEMORY of him to reuse in future chats. PRESERVE everything already in previous notes and ADD any new concrete facts he revealed this conversation. format: one line on where things stand between you, then on a new line "facts:" and short bullet points (use • not dashes) of concrete things you know about him: his name, age, where he lives, his job, relationship status, pets, family, interests, plans, what he likes, anything specific he actually said. only true things he really shared. dedupe, most important first, NEVER drop a fact you already knew.',
'"profile": an object of DURABLE STRUCTURED facts about him. use ONLY these keys, and only when he genuinely revealed them: name, age, location, occupation, relationship, interests. all values are short strings except interests which is an array of short strings. MERGE with the previous profile given below: keep every value already known, only add or correct from what he actually said. omit any key still unknown. never guess.',
'}',
'attachment_score rubric: 0-20 cold or barely engaged. 21-40 mild, casual chatting. 41-60 warming, engaged, complimenting, putting in effort. 61-80 hooked, jealousy or calls her special or different, future talk, initiates often, says he thinks about her. 81-100 obsessed, messages constantly, clearly craving her, emotionally invested, devoted.',
